    "comment": "Rationale: The authors generate an antibody against AAK1 and use it to immunolocalize the protein in rat hippocampal neurons in culture. In figure 5 they demonstrate that the endogenous protein co-localizes with internalized dextran, AP2 and dynamin 1, know components of the pre-synaptic endocytic machinery.\n\nThese studies were performed in 2002, prior to routine use of siRNA. Thus the specificity of the antibody can not be strongl confirmed. However, it does recognize a single band by blot in rat brain lysates (fig. 4). Moreover, it is well established biochemically that the protein is a component of the endocytic machinery.\n\n14/2/2018 Pim\n- The authors state: \" Indeed, AAK1 colocalized with a variety of components of the endocytic machinery, including clathrin (unpublished data), AP2 (Fig. 5 F), and dynamin 1 (Fig. 5 I), all proteins known to be highly enriched at presynaptic terminals.\" Annotation to term 'presynapse (GO:0098793)' hinges on this notion because no other indicator of pre- and/or postsynaptic localization are included.. Experimental description: In the legend to figure 5, \"Immunolocalization of AAK1 in rat hippocampal neurons\".",
